Stream Name: „ÄêV-Saikyo After Talk„ÄëThank you for all the support!!!
Writing Entry:
TSB‚Äôs First Tourney!

Despite placing 17th, TSB had grown and achieved a lot in V-Saikyo, being the first full EN team to participate. With Altare as the 3-Points Monster, the Ratt Queen‚Äôs gaming instinct, and Axel's Zone predictions and IGL, they trained vigorously (and with high spirits) for a month and improved rapidly, earning a name for themselves amongst the other teams and their viewers.

It's a bittersweet ending, no matter what they'd have placed. Everyone was so invested that there's a lingering sentimentality when it's finally over. Being their first time in a proper competitive tourney, there were a lot of things they learned and experienced, making for a great story full of fun and stressful moments.

Altare, despite only joining at first to help his friends, learned about how big V-Saikyo is, and what an amazing opportunity it was to get themselves out there. Axel was able to improve and felt more confident in his IGL-ing, but decided he might try being a fragger next time.

Most importantly, this made Axel interested in joining more competitive games and to make friends with many different people, potentially opening up more opportunities for the future. Thanks to TSB, he was able to be closer friends with his teammates and coaches, and made many great memories with them that he'd cherish forever.

Stream Name: [Birthday Stream!!!] Celebrating my 2nd birthday!!! feat. Papa Syrios
Writing Entry:
Let‚Äôs reminisce about Aniki's ‚Äò‚Äò2nd birthday‚Äô‚Äô with a wholesome (well‚Ä¶for once >:3) and chill father-son bonding talk. Who‚Äôs the special guest, you ask? Of course, it‚Äôs the one and only Papa Syrios <3
- First off, Papa Syrios‚Äô avatar‚Äôs so cool. He‚Äôs Pretty shy but he‚Äôs trying his best for the Axelotls! :D
- One of the precious streams as Jerry was being mentioned in here. He was sick and needed to be taken to the Vet a few times. :‚Äô((
- Throw your Q&A: Mostly Anime, Games and JPOP ( A lot of interesting stuff to tackle!)
 - Papa Syrios has been influenced by Japanese Culture since Kindergarten. Wow!  At 20 years old, the first time he played games was on a Super Nintendo ES with his close cousin.
- It's Merch Time! (While Papa Syrios works in the background) Aniki‚Äôs Nihongo Jouzou segment was actually an ear-candy moment 0///0
- A few top picks from Papa Syrios if you want to check it out: Zero 4 Champ, Kamen Rider (V3, Faiz), Super Robot Wars, Megazone 23, Doraemon and Queen Millenia.
- If the timing is right then Papa Syrios will come back to art, but more preferred traditional than digital. Not a natural artist he said, but Axel says otherwise.
- When it comes to booze; beer is the best. Maybe with a good wine, and Vodka on the side. No hard stuff though. ( Kanpai!)
- He loves to cook what people enjoy to eat: From a simple Steak to Fried Rice, name it.~
- Papa Syrios‚Äô chosen JP Idols: If you want a touch of disco, folk, jazz, Latin, and R&B then you might need to hear the lovely Nakamori Akina. On the other hand for hip-hop, EDM, and J-pop then AKB 48 is a great choice too with their cute aesthetic!

Honestly just a small recap of Axel working on his degree while still working and streaming for us, just a little "we're proud of you" thing. (Exact details I don't know just yet, maybe even written like a graduation card.)
Writing Entry:
Dear Axel,

YOU DID IT! YOU GRADUATED (from university)! 

From what you said, it took a while. A lot of starts and stops, but that‚Äôs OK. Everyone‚Äôs path is different. That you kept going, even when times were tough, is admirable. That you did all that, helped take care of your family and pets, held a steady job, and entertained a bunch of little idiots like us is absolutely incredible! It‚Äôs hard enough just to work a part time job during uni, let alone a full time one. 

We saw your frustrations. When you were tired and annoyed, when you probably wanted nothing more than to just sit down in silence, when you had late nights. But you would still be there, streaming, recording, singing, and working hard. We couldn‚Äôt do much for you, but we hope that, in some small way, all of us were able to make those rough days better. You were always there for us when we needed it, so we wanted to be there for you too. 

Really and truly, congratulations, Axel. We‚Äôre all so proud of you and everything you‚Äôve accomplished.  

Love, 
The Axelotls

Writing Entry:
A Very Normal 3D Off-Collab (Boys in the Shower Room Edition) 

- Instead of proper introductions, start by slapping each other's butts! (This was not rehearsed) 
- It's Friday the 13th! Altare is constantly teleporting into Bettel, Bettel has nosferatu hands, and Flayon‚Äôs neck broke from fooling around too much. Everything is fine. 
- Altare, who is the most normal of them all, goes around talking to police officers and cashiers, asking random questions like why the stop sign is shaped that way. That's our psychopathic very normal Leader!
- Story time! The boys met up, went to Altare's place riding his beautiful steed, ate some cookies and pizza and‚Äì oh, Flayon has just killed Altare by hugging him.
- Moving on! They got bagels, met with a friend and went for karaoke, where they got scammed persuaded to buy a giant bottle of ‚ÄúNot Bettel 1‚Äù for a 2-hour session. It cost $400 but hey, they got to keep the bottle!
- Bettel is not scared of Flayon at all. Especially knowing that Flayon watches him sleep, and occasionally sleepwalks and sleep talks with no recollection of it in the morning. How pleasant!
- The boys have an arm wrestling match, to which Bettel wins against Altare with his killer right arm! Surely his left arm is just as‚Äì oh, Altare obliterates him easily. But at least he has a killer right arm! 
- For absolutely no reason other than the hee hee hahas, they do another round of butt kicking‚Äì except this time Altare's crotch suffers the consequences. What a fun time! 
- They talk about going on a 3 AM walk together, which was actually kinda nice and relaxing and not at all creepy. It felt like a filler episode of an anime where the characters bond and we can feel their growth. 
- Other fun things the boys do that are completely normal and fun: Furb Doll shenanigans, group pushups, playing limbo until their backs hurt, pouring water down Bettel‚Äôs pants, and practicing viral dance moves! Truly a ‚Äúboys in the shower room‚Äù experience!

Writing: A letter or list including the fashion things that we learned from the boys (not necessarily the correct answers lol)
Writing Entry:
Dear Axel and Altare, 

It was great seeing that all of you and the rest of TEMPUS made it into the gala somehow. Thank you for also teaching us very important fashion tips, such as how derby shoes have peaky blinders, your tie should be as wide as your sleeve width, your belt should be the same color as your tie, and how trinity knots, when drawn, do not look like their name at all. We also learned from Leader that ‚ÄúAxel stinks‚Äù and that the acrylic stands ‚Äúuh‚Ä¶yeah they look cool, hey?‚Äù It was super entertaining, and I really hope we can experience TEMPUS having more fun together like this in the future!

Stream Name: „Äê3D Celebration Collab!!!„ÄëThank you for celebrating this moment with us!!!
Writing Entry:
I was feeling extremely emotional and proud after the 3D debut and ShinySpicy 3D concert. The feeling flew away after this legendary "Post 3D zatsu" off collab though. : D 

Jk. It was one of the funniest streams and peak Shiny Spicy dynamic. Just bros being bros, right? You guys are definitely not guilty after all the stuff you guys put Toramane through (bless him for putting the VOD through procedure and putting out the 2min VOD for us to have some sort of memory token). It was so fun seeing you two just messing around and being silly together. Hope to see another off-collab from HQ and just hearing you guys laughing like that again.
